info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued April 20 at 3:01AM CDT until April 21 at 1:00PM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM THIS MORNING TO 1 PM CDT FRIDAY... * WHAT...Heavy snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 6 to 12 inches. Highest amounts from International Falls and points west. * WHERE...Koochiching, North St. Louis and North Itasca Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Bois Forte Band, Deer Creek and, Nett Lake areas. * WHEN...From 7 AM this morning to 1 PM CDT Friday. * IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. The hazardous conditions could impact the morning or evening commute. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A wintry mix may occur at times this morning into early afternoon. Heaviest snow to occur this afternoon into tonight.
info.instruction: If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in your vehicle in case of an emergency. The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1. Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or 511wi.gov for Wisconsin.
